Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper is primarily focused on the concept of subgame perfect equilibrium in multiplayer games played on graphs, which falls under the domain of game theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for computing the set of constraints characterizing the set of SPE outcomes in quantitative reachability games, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with multiplayer games with objectives, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence research. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses logical reasoning to establish the complexity of the constrained existence problem for SPE in quantitative reachability games. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper establishes the PSPACE-completeness of the constrained existence problem for SPE in quantitative reachability games, which falls under the domain of computational complexity.
